news.title: Concorde Group wants to touch revenue of Rs 800 crore by 2026
news.para: Concorde Group is in talks to finalise projects having development potential of about 1.5-2 million sq ft which we expect to launch in the next six quarters, said Nesara B.S., chairman of the company.

news.title: China's Powerlong Real Estate warns of debt default risk
news.para: In an exchange filing, Powerlong also said it has not made an interest payment of $15.9 million under 5.95% senior notes due April 2025 issued by the company. These notes are listed on the Singapore Exchange.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP seals six houses in Sushant Lok 2 from where stores, workshops operated
news.para: Since October, under the orders of the district town planner (enforcement), DTCP has sealed around 500 properties for running commercial activities illegally, while notices have been served to more than 750 violators.

news.title: Madurai: Auction of granite quarries called off as activist warns of legal steps
news.para: Addressing reporters, Mugilan had warned the government that the residents of the three villages would move court if the government did not withdraw the tender notification and auction.

news.title: HCL to sell office assets in Bengaluru
news.para: The software services company, HCL, is looking to divest its special economic zone campus, situated in the Jigani industrial area, covering 27 acres with a total area of 1.6 million square feet.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body again looks to auction Bodakdev plots
news.para: An auction proposal put before the standing committee on Wednesday set the total reserve price for these eight plots at Rs 835.77 crore.

news.title: Pune: Hurdles continue for citizens to carry out online corrections in 7/12 extracts
news.para: The revenue department had since last year allowed citizens to opt for an online software to make changes in mutation extracts. But citizens have demanded better coordination between departments to iron out issues.

news.title: Pune civic body mulls amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: A discount on penalty would be offered as part of this programme. Property owners in Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) areas may avail the benefits of the scheme through Lok Adalat.

news.title: Greater Noida development body to allot 22 commercial plots
news.para: Informing this, an official spokesperson said that the deadline for registration in this plot allocation scheme is set for December 8 and the entire process will be completed through the SBI’S e-tendering portal.

news.title: Over 100 premises up for auction in Pimpri Chinchwad
news.para: The civic body will soon start a process to auction a total of 109 properties across the city. A total of Rs 4 crore in tax is due from the owners of these properties.

news.title: White Lotus Group raises Rs 150 crore
news.para: The capital raised in this funding round will be allocated to fuel White Lotus Group's growth, strengthen the brand's presence in Bengaluru & expand into Hyderabad, Pune, Chennai and other major cities.

news.title: Indore: Clear property tax dues on December 9 & get rebate on surcharge
news.para: IMC officials said, as per MP Municipal Corporation Act, 1956, up to 100% rebate has been offered on surcharge on clearing Rs 50,000 of property tax dues, followed by 50% rebate on dues between Rs 50,000 and upto Rs 1 lakh, rebate of 25% on clearing of property tax and surcharge dues totalling above Rs 1 lakh.

news.title: DC directs Mysuru development body to stop issuing khatas; activist lauds decision
news.para: Going forward, only local bodies will have the authority to issue land titles. The move is anticipated to benefit site owners and potential buyers in Mysuru and surrounding areas, garnering support from activists, as well as the public.

news.title: Jaipur development body razes four illegal colonies
news.para: Dharmendra Kumar Yadav, chief controller of enforcement department, said that in Chandlai area, private agricultural land was levelled without the approval of JDA and without land conversion.

news.title: Europe's Signa toppled in property rout
news.para: Controlled by Austrian magnate Rene Benko, Signa group is an owner of New York's Chrysler Building as well as several high-profile projects and department stores across Germany, Austria and Switzerland.

news.title: Gujarat RERA 2.0 portal ensures compliance with GST, income tax regulations
news.para: Previously, some developers would submit outdated photographs in quarterly progress reports (QPR) and provide misinformation about project completion to tax authorities to manage their profit tax liability.

news.title: Greater Noida: Rs 2 crore dues not cleared, movie theatre sealed in Grand Venice Mall
news.para: Ankit Kumar, the Sadar SDM, said while Rera had issued three recovery certificates against Bhasin Infotech and Infrastructures Ltd – the developer of the mall – the consumer forum slapped one.

news.title: Maharashtra government cuts transfer fee for slum rehabilitation flats by 50%
news.para: Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis had made an announcement on this at a conference of cooperative housing societies in Mumbai in May this year.
